"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"899c07",
"children":[
"Hypercapnic respiratory (ventilatory) failure occurs when alveolar ventilation is inadequate and the level of CO",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"2"
]
},
" increases in the blood. Because oxygenation also depends on ventilation, patients are often hypoxic as well. However, hypoxia will often improve with supplemental oxygen. Chronic hypercapnic respiratory failure occurs most often in patients with:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"403c71",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"chronic obstructive pulmonary disease",
"children":[
"COPD"
]
},
" and asthma"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"21851c",
"children":[
"neuromuscular disease (",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"myasthenia gravis",
"children":[
"MG"
]
},
","
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"amyotrophic lateral sclerosis",
"children":[
"ALS"
]
},
","
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"multiple sclerosis",
"children":[
"MS"
]
},
")"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"46d5a8",
"children":[
"restrictive lung diseases (chest wall skeletal disorders, obesity)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b50432",
"children":[
"depressed respiratory drive (opioids and sedatives)"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_pm_s19_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"fa6a5a",
"children":[
"Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"027b61",
"children":[
"All patients suspected of having hypercapnic respiratory failure should have arterial blood gas analysis even if hypoxemia resolves with oxygen administration."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"8d3d50",
"children":[
"In patients with neuromuscular disease, ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"pulmonary function test",
"children":[
"PFT"
]
},
"s"
]
},
" show restriction on spirometry and lung volume measurement but normal diffusing capacity."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_pm_s19_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"88b1de",
"children":[
"Patients with respiratory muscle weakness, obesity-hypoventilation syndrome, and disorders of ventilatory control first hypoventilate during ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"rapid eye movement",
"children":[
"REM"
]
},
" sleep. Order polysomnography if nocturnal hypoventilation is suspected (daytime sleepiness, nocturnal awakenings, morning headaches)."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_pm_s19_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Test Yourself"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7866cc",
"children":[
"Test Yourself"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"45f807",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"A 36-year-old man with myotonic dystrophy awakens at night gasping for air and experiences increasing fatigue. Cardiopulmonary examination is normal. Neurologic examination shows 4+/5 strength in all muscle groups."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"5b4cd2",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For diagnosis, choose nocturnal hypercapnic respiratory failure. For management, elect polysomnography."
]
}
]
}
]
},
